The Adamawa state House of Assembly on Wednesday appointed principal officers. Announcing the new principal officers during a plenary session, the Speaker, Aminu Iya-Abbas, named Hamman Tukur Yettisuri (Jada/Mbulo) as Majority Leader. Japhet Kefas (Gombi) emerged as Deputy Majority Leader, Ayuba Kwada (Michika) as Chief Whip and Andawa Donglock (Guyuk) as Deputy Chief Whip. Others are Mohammed Mutawali (Girei) as Minority Leader, Abdullahi Umar (Toungo) as Deputy Minority Leader, Ibrahim Musa (Mayo Belwa) as Minority Whip and Shuaibu Musa (Mubi North) as DeputyÂ  Minority Whip. SDP beats PDP to produce minority leader in Adamawa Assembly Kaduna 5th Assembly names principal officers EFCC detains Kano speaker, principal officers Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin